\lson We'll show you how to battle in RPG system, with Action Turn Battle (ATB) Style.
First, there are 5 command menus in the window.
\c[5]Attack\c[0], the basic attack from the player.
Second, there is special attack from player.
\c[5]Magic\c[0], is magical attack from \c[3]Mage\c[0] or \c[3]Priest\c[0] class.
\c[5]Signature Skill\c[0] is command to let the actor use own signature skill.
Each character has different signature skill. This skill uses \c[5]Limit Gauge\c[0]
on the lower right on the screen.
third command for each characters in the battlefield.
And the fourth command is \c[5]Move\c[0] command.
This command will allow you to shift battler backward or
forward in battlefield. Each grid position has benefit
Front row position is good for attacker
and increases hit-accuracy, but decreases defense.
Middle row position will increases defense,
Place allies here who can fight from the middle.
Back row has an advantage for weak defense member,
but decreases attack and hit-accuracy so drastically.
And the last command is \c[5]Item\c[0] command.
It will allows you to use any items in battle, like potion, etc.
There are 5 command menus. Let's try attack the enemy first!
Next, we'll explain battle components further.
First, \c[5]Health Point (HP)\c[0]. There is HP bar below with the green color.
If you reached 0 point, you will die.
There is MP bar below with the blue color.
MP is usually used for magical skills. Mostly, some magic skills used MP.
There is a TP bar below with the purple color.
TP is commonly used for special or physical skills.
Let's try use special skill or magic skill to your foe!
there is a turn gauge. It displays each turn who will goes first.
That's all about the tutorial. You can defeat the enemy easily now!
Alright! You have completed the tutorial! Once you finished the battle, you will get \c[3]JP\c[0]
Job Points (JP) is used for learn new skills.
